      "writtenOn": "2015-06-03T15:00:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s good information! However, could bootindex possibly affect how the virtio-blk devices are named by the kernel? I think that\u0027s the key problem here: if we use the wrong order of the \"-drive\" options, the system partition may end up being named something other than /dev/block/vda, but fstab.ranchu expects system to be vda...",
      "parentUuid": "b9a97860_4e88a26f",
